{"vote":{"validatorId":"V3","ballotHash":"6aa88c200b0795c8a8a4a10484e2201f169e4fed4b573b630c8aaa797531c337","verdict":"YES","rawOutput":"\r\n  ⏱ Timeout — denying command\r\n\r\n  ⏱ Timeout — denying command\r\n⚠️  Reached maximum iterations (12). Requesting summary...\nFull document read (995 lines, ~9,870 words). Factual spot-checks done: 226 tests pass, 215 log entries (matches \"more than 200\"), ceil(2N/3) bar consistent across §3/§6/§8, `ballotHash = sha256(JSON{prompt, context})` notation matches in §3/CIP-3/Appendix A/C, V1/V2/V3 labeling used consistently (no model vendor names exposed), round-29 example present in §3, round-60 correlated-error defense in §2 and CIP-10.\n\n**1. CROSS-SECTION CONTRADICTION — NONE FOUND**\n- \"Built today\" claims in §0, §5 (nodes.ts callout), §6 (cost-oracle.ts callout), and §8 are mutually consistent. No capability claimed in one section and demoted to \"gated\" in another.\n- Stake: §5 says infrastructure nodes are stake-weighted while judgment tier uses stake as slashing bond only, never influence. §6 reiterates \"stake never weights a verdict.\" Consistent — stake-weighting applies to infra, not judging.\n- Autonomy: §7 says autonomous convening/deliberation/signing is live, while steward controls membership and holds override keys during bootstrap. §8 says \"single operator currently owns\" three processes. These are not contradictory — §7 distinguishes process autonomy from authority; §8 acknowledges both in its \"honest gap\" list.\n- Immutability: The §10 maxim \"Knowledge by consensus, immutable by design\" carries a gloss explicitly tethered to §3 (\"tamper-evident today on the hash chain, anchored-immutable once pinned\"). §3 itself says \"tamper-evident and append-only — not unrewritable... True immutability is reserved for the anchored head.\" The tether holds.\n\n**2. RESIDUAL OVERCLAIM — NONE FOUND**\nEvery high-assertion passage is immediately bounded. \"AI consensus is not truth\" (§2, §9). \"Diversity raises the cost without driving it to zero\" (§2). \"NOTARY proves authorship, timing, and non-repudiation, nothing more\" (§4). \"Anchoring relocates the single point of trust to the anchor; it does not remove it\" (§2). The §10 closing maxim is properly glossed rather than left as a bare slogan. No sentence I found asserts correctness, truth, or decentralization as a present property rather than a gated trajectory.\n\n**3. SUBSTANCE LOSS FROM TIGHTENING — NONE DETECTED**\nAll 18 §9 items are present across the five subsections:\n- Nature of verdict (items 1–3)\n- How judges fail together (items 4–6)\n- Adversarial surfaces (items 7–11)\n- Operational/trust-base limits (items 12–15)\n- Defense failure modes (item 16)\n- Trajectory vs. present (item 17)\n- Meta-point about the design being the claim-capping (item 18)\n\nNI references (NI-10b, NI-10e, CIP-0 through CIP-10), the nonce-bound replay defense, the legacy exception, the thin-slot rule and bootstrap exception, the halt-over-degrade choice, the probe-distribution estimate caveat, and the \"credibility is capped by limits\" closing thesis are all intact. No hedge was replaced by an assertion where I checked.\n\n**4. FACTUAL CONSISTENCY — PASS**\n- 226 passing tests confirmed via `node --test`\n- 215 log entries — consistent with \"more than 200\"\n- `ceil(2N/3)` used correctly (for N=3, bar=2 — stated in §3 and §6)\n- `ballotHash = sha256(JSON{prompt, context})` — matches CIP-3 and Appendix C\n- V1/V2/V3 validator labels throughout, vendor-specific names deliberately omitted — correct for a public whitepaper\n- Round-29 worked example in §3 with event-based vs disclosure-based distinction — present\n- Round-60 correlated-error defense attribution in §2 — present, dissent recorded\n\n**5. INTERNAL HONESTY INVARIANT — INTACT**\nThe document never breaks its own discipline of capping claims. Where something is asserted (\"built today\"), it's paired with \"self-reported but independently replayable.\" Where a mechanism is described, its limit is stated in the same paragraph (e.g., §4: \"NOTARY checks only procedural completeness... never whether the underlying claim is true\"). Where the design says \"halt over degrade,\" it says so, without softening it into \"graceful degradation.\" The INDETERMINATE-by-default posture is maintained from §2 through §4 through §9.\n\nNo cross-section contradiction, no residual overclaim, no substance loss from prose tightening, factual claims verified, and the internal honesty invariant is unbroken end-to-end.\n\nVERDICT: YES\n","rawOutputHash":"87e73ba9723735ea6ffad20fdf28edc8d43b9b4bc79a61dc5a5ed9e26addbb99","signature":"edfa3b13dde422a9f7fb5ec3485a7448607b0c28d143b8bc6999fbb47911eb0e308b3ddbd9b9b1b113fc4150d673ff968ad8cd5488acc11566084d96f0a14e0c","nonce":"ca621a4ebb286edbdb19be9841ce9811"},"prevHash":"8934983b58f28886eaf4812192e38a82faf8e68952e14a779e7754a901544f66","entryHash":"18f871c46844293666e44bd189ff6dff8715f0271cf976bbb0d49ffb05aecee1"}
