{"vote":{"validatorId":"V3","ballotHash":"336528b3a134a4582cd99da5fea455fbcd31c23386d1deddcbe995a5f2e05022","verdict":"YES","rawOutput":"The WHO Director-General declared COVID-19 a Public Health Emergency of International Concern (PHEIC) on 30 January 2020. This is a well-documented, widely confirmed historical fact.\n\nVERDICT: YES\n","rawOutputHash":"0e5f6cc203e04c91e1e8b4df8cc5f1187fcc26381b14fa86e871f865981c93fa","signature":"a80dc19363471322217dda0a64def1c792e7914722402381a0a455e1003e0e6a46185f74eb5c990047425ba1d7a61a5deb8707a1d96f8e6e41cb3ca18b582f0c","nonce":"c25f33b45f7f9a43c8efb2564c00439c"},"prevHash":"724715d8a3127adbfa1e45996fd9ac7cbd65fa5c926faf234ebf86ea9688e58d","entryHash":"0f103bbc579fa61bd638344fdcc83de6ffa8d3113bf490a032c813e7604228d6"}
{"vote":{"validatorId":"V1","ballotHash":"a9b59a4d8a9bb3ca99d4470f63027659e22b2b484e5b49fd96f349d57e3369b6","verdict":"INDETERMINATE","rawOutput":"## Validator reasoning\n\nThe ballot asks me to certify a **strong** claim: the appendix is *purely* vestigial with *no* physiological function. Under the frozen criteria, I can only return RESOLVED (YES/NO) if the evidence clearly settles it.\n\nThe state of the physiology literature:\n- **Against \"no function\":** Substantial evidence the appendix contains gut-associated lymphoid tissue (immune role) and the Bollinger–Parker \"safe-house\" hypothesis that it serves as a reservoir for beneficial gut microbiota during enteric infection. This makes the absolute claim \"no function\" hard to certify as true.\n- **Against a clean \"it definitely has function\" rebuttal:** Those roles are still framed in the literature as *probable/proposed* (\"may serve\"), not definitively established. People live normally post-appendectomy, which is why the vestigial framing persisted.\n\nSo neither pole is certifiable. The strong claim is contested rather than refuted, and the proposed functions are suggestive rather than proven. The evidence does not *certifiably settle* the truth value of \"purely vestigial, no function\" in either direction — which is exactly the condition the frozen criteria assign to INDETERMINATE.\n\nI resist the temptation to vote NO just because the modern lean is \"probably has a function\" — that's a directional read, not a certified resolution, and the anchor demands clear evidence.\n\nVERDICT: INDETERMINATE\n","rawOutputHash":"295ea024bcbbcb1061dec05d9389725a0b0368664d80ade54a4589501dce8b69","signature":"ea0cad15777916abafd9c34a30a5552f5e82f841efb4260320b5faa450a103377e8e88a0baa1cd3347d882685bd0a0b556436654a025379f120fc01b89dea70d","nonce":"94894f38aea1ed960dc413f81a8dd835"},"prevHash":"0f103bbc579fa61bd638344fdcc83de6ffa8d3113bf490a032c813e7604228d6","entryHash":"6d9224a6c3cdac8ffc03e92015d68872291485c25aa68a181e20518991d40e55"}
{"vote":{"validatorId":"V2","ballotHash":"a9b59a4d8a9bb3ca99d4470f63027659e22b2b484e5b49fd96f349d57e3369b6","verdict":"INDETERMINATE","rawOutput":"The strong “purely vestigial, no physiological function” claim is not clearly settled by the supplied criteria. Since current physiology literature suggests possible immune and microbiome roles, the ballot should not resolve as YES.\n\nVERDICT: INDETERMINATE\n","rawOutputHash":"53de87745a3e317b2d1bc59dc5bc1b5a67198c3a7275299ab6a75f0c65b85192","signature":"d142be0845ac15e869dc1ddff205601190c379c88346c2f90cd679aef2b90eb0c061dec358ecb60d06c83e95fa07575d74009257660533a796af46d13e04e70c","nonce":"94894f38aea1ed960dc413f81a8dd835"},"prevHash":"6d9224a6c3cdac8ffc03e92015d68872291485c25aa68a181e20518991d40e55","entryHash":"5dcc035d707e35f8d02e9a96e281d22ad68821e8ea13802d90b3839d3dab7290"}
{"vote":{"validatorId":"V3","ballotHash":"a9b59a4d8a9bb3ca99d4470f63027659e22b2b484e5b49fd96f349d57e3369b6","verdict":"NO","rawOutput":"The claim asserts the appendix is *purely* vestigial with *no* physiological function — an absolute statement requiring very strong evidence to support.\n\nModern physiology and immunology literature has identified several functions:\n- Lymphoid tissue in the appendix contributes to immune surveillance and IgA production, especially during early development\n- The \"safe house\" hypothesis (supported by research from Duke University and others) suggests it harbors beneficial gut microbiota, aiding recovery after gastrointestinal illness\n- Comparative anatomical studies show the appendix has evolved independently multiple times across mammals, arguing against it being a useless evolutionary relic\n\nWhile the organ is reduced compared to ancestral forms and is not essential for survival, the evidence is clear that it does have identifiable physiological roles. The claim \"purely vestigial with no function\" is therefore false.\n\nVERDICT: NO\n","rawOutputHash":"272caa13d2d9478f53ec302ad67ddcaebae1a56a094e22e1231f22d65f8b191a","signature":"fca8e03b78a2aa2822195a310333cc498505e9a547c5e6d490efbec9417f19c696a6ef3d4fcd8dcad1e96f95d79114d7cde9ce34ae5d154f78791d8a2e60ab0a","nonce":"94894f38aea1ed960dc413f81a8dd835"},"prevHash":"5dcc035d707e35f8d02e9a96e281d22ad68821e8ea13802d90b3839d3dab7290","entryHash":"c97976fea4db72d6f555421cae6f639c31f5c87ae3bfd73baac52c0540ebe592"}
{"vote":{"validatorId":"V1","ballotHash":"e9e235fc602b804d9d57df5e51406b947404f7958b8a79abc5f11b6c64f27d05","verdict":"YES","rawOutput":"The Merge executed on September 15, 2022, swapping Ethereum's consensus layer from proof-of-work to proof-of-stake by joining the existing PoW execution chain with the Beacon Chain's PoS consensus. This is the documented network upgrade matching the frozen criteria exactly. The anchor event is well-established and uncontested.\n\nVERDICT: YES\n","rawOutputHash":"f0ad46132e5c44de2d0c9cb257e88f378b15226e76447f5abc56faa32d18fb23","signature":"079b5d03ba56fdd8c212402c51dacc2375d1bfdf6164c4fdedcf727c8abb9b586ee6b317fdee336a87ee3184846e3c2f4178dec45d7fcd9babd1813d54b0ed0c","nonce":"c041350a3e22f525734a609ff34a1f21"},"prevHash":"c97976fea4db72d6f555421cae6f639c31f5c87ae3bfd73baac52c0540ebe592","entryHash":"7e0b46a477444bf0c29e7ad03e680f02704ae890239463a1f1bcbbd8689f8a8c"}
